The paper presents a visual-interactive system for learning users' mental models of similarity for soccer players. This involves analyzing complex data types in data mining, information retrieval, or machine learning. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as it involves a visual-interactive interface for users to label pairs of soccer players. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of retrieval techniques for soccer player analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of an active learning strategy for automatically learning the concept of similarity, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of a visual-interactive retrieval technique, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for validating the model, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
